text: Craig Van der Wath (born 28 June 1966 in Bloemfontein) is a South African professional squash player. He reached a career high of 21 in the world. He represented his country in the Commonwealth Games. He has won the World Masters Squash Championships a record 6 times. ==References== Category:1966 births Category:Living people Category:South African male squash players
